## 7. Compliance Checklist — Master

### Phase 0: System Design

- [ ] `CopyrightChecker` implemented with AI opt-out patterns (EN/FR/ES/DE/IT/NL)
- [ ] Hard block implemented for BLOCKED documents — never reaches LLM
- [ ] Paraphrase constraint injected into system prompt for RESTRICTED documents
- [ ] `documents.copyright_status` enum defined: `pending | clear | restricted | blocked`
- [ ] `documents.copyright_reason` field exists for storing matched pattern
- [ ] `guardrail_audit` JSONB field exists in `document_analyses` table

### Phase 1: Document Ingestion

- [ ] Copyright scan runs on upload — not only on analysis
- [ ] `copyright_status` set to `pending` on upload
- [ ] `copyright_status` updated to final classification after scan
- [ ] BLOCKED documents flagged to Admin immediately on upload

### Phase 2: AI Analysis

- [ ] Layer 1 (pre-LLM) check runs before CrewAI/DSPy/OpenAI call
- [ ] BLOCKED documents raise error and return HTTP 451 — never processed
- [ ] RESTRICTED documents receive paraphrase instruction in system prompt
- [ ] Layer 2 (post-LLM) validates source_excerpts for verbatim content
- [ ] All extracted rules/plans include `source_document_id` and `source_excerpt`
- [ ] `guardrail_audit` stored with every `document_analyses` record

### Phase 3: Human Review

- [ ] Admin can see copyright status per document in the review interface
- [ ] BLOCKED documents shown with reason and "Manual review required" notice
- [ ] RESTRICTED source_excerpts labeled as paraphrased in the UI

### Phase 4: Ongoing Compliance

- [ ] Annual re-scan of all active documents for updated opt-out declarations
- [ ] Copyright compliance tested in CI/CD (opt-out detection unit tests)
- [ ] New opt-out patterns added as publisher policies evolve
- [ ] Compliance incident log reviewed quarterly

