## 8. Legal Reference Quick Guide

| Topic | Directive / Regulation | Article | Summary |
|---|---|---|---|
| Reproduction right | InfoSoc 2001/29/EC | Art. 2 | Any reproduction requires license or exception |
| Communication to public | InfoSoc 2001/29/EC | Art. 3 | Distribution to users requires license or exception |
| Transient copy exception | InfoSoc 2001/29/EC | Art. 5(1) | Temporary RAM copies OK if technically necessary |
| TDM research exception | DSM 2019/790 | Art. 3 | Research orgs only, no opt-out possible |
| TDM commercial exception | DSM 2019/790 | Art. 4 | Any use, **opt-out overrides** |
| Database extraction | Database Directive 96/9/EC | Art. 7 | Substantial part extraction requires license |
| AI copyright compliance | EU AI Act 2024/1689 | Art. 53(1)(c) | GPAI providers must respect copyright |
| Training data transparency | EU AI Act 2024/1689 | Art. 53(1)(d) | Publish summary of training data |
| AI output disclosure | EU AI Act 2024/1689 | Art. 50 | Label AI-generated content |
| Infopaq doctrine | CJEU C-5/08 | — | 11 words may constitute protected expression |
| Moral rights | Berne Convention | Art. 6bis | Attribution + integrity rights — not waivable |
| Enforcement | IPRED 2004/48/EC | Arts. 7–12 | Injunctions, damages, provisional measures |
